Dependency injection is pattern where object's dependencies are provided from outside. Not created inside object. This make code more testable and flexible.

Example: Instead of:

```javascript
class Logger {
  constructor() {
    this.logger = new WinstonLogger();
  }
}
```

Use interface:

```javascript
class Logger {
  constructor(logger) {
    this.logger = logger;
  }
}
```

Now `Logger` doesn't create `WinstonLogger` itself. It gets it injected. Easy to swap out for different logger in tests.

